translated: Baagee, Herman Theodor, councilman, Partille, born on July 8, 1895 in Virke, Malmöh, as the son of Johan B. and Maria Eugenia Kin-berg. Married in 1924 to farm. candidate Hanna Axelsson. Children: Peder born in 1926, law student, Thomas born in 1929, university student. Studied at Lund University, graduated with a law degree in 1914, appointed as an associate notary in Skånska hovrätt in 1919, served as a temporary notary in Gbgs rådhusrätt in 1922, became a clerk at the city actuary's office in 1929, appointed as an assessor in 1931, and became a councilman in 1938. He was a lecturer at Gbgs handelsinstitut from 1929 to 1939. He was chairman of the tax council in Gbgs och Bohus län from 1930 to 1939, chairman of the Gbgs krististyr from 1939, and chairman of the association Skyddsvärnet in Gbg since 1940. His hobbies included hiking and cycling. Awarded the Order of Vasa.
